                    <h1 style="color:black">The importance of SMU UH</h1>
                    <p1>
                        The establishment of Provo's Social Media Usage and Mental Health committee (SMU MH committee) reflects a proactive response by the city government to the escalating concerns surrounding mental health in the context of burgeoning social media usage. With a noticeable increase in anxiety, depression, and social isolation, the local government recognizes the need to investigate the intricate relationship between digital connectivity and the well-being of their community members. The creation of the SMU MH committee demonstrates a commitment to understanding the specific influences and stressors that social media may impose on residents' mental health. The acquisition of a relevant dataset from Plainsville, a neighboring community with similar demographics, underscores the committee's dedication to thorough research and data-driven insights. By delving into these connections, the committee aims to formulate informed strategies and interventions to promote a healthier and more resilient community in the face of evolving digital landscapes.
                    </p1>
